genetic activation of the projections from the ICx to the dorsal periaqueductal gray is sufficient for provoking flight behaviours. Our results suggest that ACx can both amplify innate acoustic-motor responses and directly drive flight behaviours in the absence of sound input through corticocollicular projections to ICx. Such corticofugal control may be a general feature of innate defense circuits across sensory modalities.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa62f3cf058f610008259","authors":["Xiong, Xiaorui R","Liang, Feixue","Zingg, Brian","Ji, Xu-Ying","Ibrahim, Leena A","Tao, Huizhong W","Zhang, Li I"],"doi":"10.1038/ncomms8224","first_seen_on":"2015-06-13T10:10:03+00:00","funders":["niehs"],"issns":["2041-1723"],"journal":"Nature Communications","links":["http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26068082?dopt=Abstract&utm_source=dlvr.it&utm_medium=twitter","http://www.nature.com/ncomms/2015/150611/ncomms8224/full/ncomms8224.html"],"pmid":"26068082","pubdate":"2015-06-13T22:03:08+00:00","publisher_subjects":[{"name":"Multidisciplinary","scheme":"era"}],"subjects":["biology","science"],"title":"Auditory cortex controls sound-driven innate defense behaviour through corticofugal projections to inferior colliculus","type":"article","volume":"6","mendeley_url":"http://www.mendeley.com/research/auditory-cortex-controls-sounddriven-innate-defense-behaviour-through-corticofugal-projections-infer"},"altmetric_score":{"score":1.25,"score_history":{"1y":0,"6m":0,"3m":0,"1m":0,"1w":0,"6d":0,"5d":0,"4d":0,"3d":0,"2d":0,"1d":0,"at":1.25},"context_for_score":{"all":{"total_number_of_other_articles":5228922,"mean":6.1649666082185,"rank":2587939,"this_scored_higher_than_pct":47,"this_scored_higher_than":2483577,"rank_type":"exact","sample_size":5228922,"percentile":47},"similar_age_3m":{"total_number_of_other_articles":178302,"mean":8.6266538606067,"rank":90741,"this_scored_higher_than_pct":44,"this_scored_higher_than":79771,"rank_type":"exact","sample_size":178302,"percentile":44},"this_journal":{"